{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/PMTiles","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Working with PMTiles"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Starting MapLibre iOS 6.10.0, using "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/docs.protomaps.com\/pmtiles\/","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" as a data source is supported. You can prefix your vector tile source with "},{"code":"pmtiles:\/\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to load a PMTiles file. The rest of the URL continue with be "},{"code":"https:\/\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to load a remote PMTiles file, "},{"code":"asset:\/\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to load an asset or "},{"code":"file:\/\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to load a local PMTiles file."}]},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"PMTiles sources currently do not support caching or offline pack downloads."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Oliver Wipfli has made a style available that combines a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":""},{"type":"text","text":" basemap togehter with Foursquare’s POI dataset. It is available in the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/wipfli\/foursquare-os-places-pmtiles"},{"type":"text","text":" repository on GitHub. The style to use is"}]},{"code":["https:\/\/raw.githubusercontent.com\/wipfli\/foursquare-os-places-pmtiles\/refs\/heads\/main\/style.json"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":null},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The neat thing about this style is that it only uses PMTiles vector sources. PMTiles can be hosted with a relatively simple file server (or file hosting service) instead of a more complex specialized tile